title: ROC Surface Analysis Under the Three-class Problems — ROCsurf
text: x, y, z vector quantiles. alpha shape parameter. beta scale parameter. p vector probabilities. n number observations. length(n) > 1, length taken number required. init_param initial paremeter values estimation method. true_param true parameter values. model selected model. default value model "GWL". method estimation method. default value method "MLE". init_index initial index value optimization calculation. empirical empirical must TRUE FALSE. alpha1 shape parameter distribution first sample. beta1 scale parameter distribution first sample. alpha2 shape parameter distribution second sample. beta2 scale parameter distribution second sample. alpha3 location parameter distribution third sample. beta3 scale parameter distribution third sample.

title: ROC Surface Analysis Under the Three-class Problems — ROCsurf
text: dG gives probability density function Gamma Distribution. dW gives probability density function Weibull Distribution. dL gives probability density function Logistic Distribution. pG gives cumulative density function Gamma Distribution. pW gives cumulative density function Weibull Distribution. pL gives cumulative density function Logistic Distribution. qG gives quantile function Gamma Distribution. qW gives quantile function Weibull Distribution. qL gives quantile function Logistic Distribution. rG gives random numbers Gamma Distribution. rW gives random numbers Weibull Distribution. rL gives random numbers Logistic Distribution. r.tc_vus gives Volume Surface (VUS) data conforms proposed three distributions. r.tc_index gives index values data conforms proposed three distributions. r.tc_graph gives ROC curve data conforms proposed three distributions.
